EventItemActionText: A motion was made that this Resolution be Approved, by Council approved by Voice Vote.
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the Delaware River Basin Commission to refrain from issuing regulations governing gas exploration and production using hydraulic fracturing and for water withdrawal for the purpose of hydraulic fracturing within the Delaware River Basin until a cumulative impact study is completed to assess the risks and inform the development of adequate regulations for hydraulic fracturing in the Delaware River Basin.
EventItemMatterName: Delaware River Basin Commission to refrain from issuing regulations governing gas exploration and production using hydraulic fracturing and for water withdrawal for the purpose of hydraulic fracturing within the Delaware River Basin.

INTRODUCTION AND READING OF BILLS

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York and the New York city building code, in relation to greenhouses.
EventItemMatterName: In relation to greenhouses.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the Metropolitan Transportation Authority to require that all contractors hired by the Authority are certified by the Society for Protective Coating in the appropriate standards for lead abatement.
EventItemMatterName: MTA to require that all contractors hired by the Authority are certified by the Society for Protective Coating in the appropriate standards for lead abatement.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Cultural Affairs, Libraries and International Intergroup Relations
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on all New Yorkers to support the One Nation Working Together movement and to participate in its march in Washington, DC on October 2, 2010.
EventItemMatterName: New Yorkers to support the One Nation Working Together movement and to participate in its march in Washington, DC on 10/2/10.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to adoption by the city of New York of the international green building code.
EventItemMatterName: Adoption by the city of NY of the international green building code.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the New York city building code, in relation to sun control devices.
EventItemMatterName: Sun control devices.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York and the New York city building code, in relation to allowing large solar rooftop installations.
EventItemMatterName: Allowing large solar rooftop installations.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the New York city building code, in relation to the installation of rooftop solar panels.
EventItemMatterName: Installation of rooftop solar panels.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to amending the New York city energy conservation code.
EventItemMatterName: Amending the New York city energy conservation code.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to regulating the use of mobile telephones while operating non-motorized transportation devices.
EventItemMatterName: Regulating the use of mobile telephones while operating non-motorized transportation devices.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Consumer Affairs
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to displaying a bill of rights and responsibilities in pedicabs.
EventItemMatterName: Displaying a bill of rights and responsibilities in pedicabs.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the installation of solar power energy systems on building walls and for ground mounted systems.
EventItemMatterName: Installation of solar power energy systems on building walls and for ground mounted systems.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York and the New York city building code, in relation to roof coating standards.
EventItemMatterName: Roof coating standards.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the Administrative Code of the City of New York to require the Department of Buildings to develop and, where appropriate, adopt existing detailed criteria for the installation of vegetated green roofs.
EventItemMatterName: Require the Dept of Buildings to develop and, where appropriate, adopt existing detailed criteria for the installation of vegetated green roofs.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York in relation to requiring photovoltaic installations on city-owned buildings.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring photovoltaic installations on city-owned buildings.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to adoption of standards and a protocol that accommodates the installation of wind energy turbines on buildings.
EventItemMatterName: Adoption of standards and a protocol that accommodates the installation of wind energy turbines on buildings.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the City of New York in relation to the installation of city-owned solar hot water systems on city-owned buildings, for privately-owned systems, and to establish a pilot program for owners of private property to install solar hot water systems.
EventItemMatterName: Installation of city-owned solar hot water systems on city-owned buildings.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to fees for the installation of solar power energy systems.
EventItemMatterName: Fees for the installation of solar power energy systems.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York in relation to creation of a Solar Map, accessible online, and to establish a Smart Solar program to help residents and businesses pursue the best solar solution for their locale.
EventItemMatterName: Creation of a Solar Map, accessible online, and to establish a Smart Solar program to help residents and businesses pursue the best solar solution for their locale.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Environmental Protection
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the Delaware River Basin Commission to refrain from issuing regulations governing gas exploration and production using hydraulic fracturing and for water withdrawal for the purpose of hydraulic fracturing within the Delaware River Basin until a cumulative impact study is completed to assess the risks and inform the development of adequate regulations for hydraulic fracturing in the Delaware River Basin.
EventItemMatterName: Delaware River Basin Commission to refrain from issuing regulations governing gas exploration and production using hydraulic fracturing and for water withdrawal for the purpose of hydraulic fracturing within the Delaware River Basin.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the New York city charter, in relation to requiring the department of education to provide data regarding student discharges.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring the department of education to provide data regarding student discharges.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to mandating bullet-resistant barriers and necessary security inside bank buildings.
EventItemMatterName: Mandating bullet-resistant barriers and necessary security inside bank buildings.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to allocation of bus stops to private bus companies.
EventItemMatterName: Allocation of bus stops to private bus companies.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Waterfronts
EventItemTitle: Resolution urging the New York State Public Service Commission to immediately set a competitive electrical rate at the Brooklyn Cruise Terminal in order to facilitate the use of shore-based electrical power by cruise ships that wish to cease idling in ports and reduce the amount of emissions released into the surrounding neighborhoods.
EventItemMatterName: NYS Public Service Commission to immediately set a competitive electrical rate at the Brooklyn Cruise Terminal.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to adopt and the Governor to sign legislation A.5851/S.4637, which relates to the repeal of the tax exemption for residual petroleum products sold by a business registered as a residual petroleum business to a consumer for exclusive use as a bunker fuel for vessels, or for use by the residual petroleum business as bunker fuel for its own vessels.
EventItemMatterName: Repeal of the tax exemption for residual petroleum products sold by a business registered as a residual petroleum business to a consumer for exclusive use as a bunker fuel for vessels. (A.5851/S.4637)

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance
EventItemTitle: Resolution approving the new designation and changes in the designation of certain organizations to receive funding in the Fiscal 2011 and Fiscal 2010 Expense Budgets.
EventItemMatterName: Approving the new designation and changes in the designation of certain organizations to receive funding in the Fiscal 2011 and Fiscal 2010 Expense Budgets.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York and the New York city building code, in relation to combined heat and power systems.
EventItemMatterName: Exempting solar panels from limits on rooftop coverage.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to, requiring the New York city police department to provide certain security measures for nonpublic schools.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring the NYPD to provide certain security measures for nonpublic schools.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Consumer Affairs
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the sale of meats contained within modified atmosphere packaging systems.
EventItemMatterName: Sale of meats contained within modified atmosphere packaging systems.

EventItemTitle: Resolution denouncing the use of fur by all clothing manufacturers and the inhumane manner in which the animals used for fur are killed.
EventItemMatterName: Denouncing the use of fur by all clothing manufacturers and the inhumane manner in which the animals used for fur are killed.

EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the use of green technologies in landmarked buildings.
EventItemMatterName: Use of green technologies in landmarked buildings.
